        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 12 at 2:55PM MDT by NWS Grand Junction CO</headline>
        <description>At 254 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles east of Ignacio, or 23 miles northeast of Navajo Dam, moving
northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pagosa Springs, Chimney Rock, Allison, Arboles, Tiffany, and
Lonetree.

This includes the following highways...
U.S. Highway 160 in Colorado between mile markers 114 and 141.
Colorado 151 between mile markers 5 and 33.
Colorado 172 near mile marker 1.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
